en: Entering Camp New York in Suippes, France

An soldier takes a photograph of the speed limit sign for "Camp New York."  Camp New York, or Camp Suippes or Camp de Tahure, was located in Suippes, France and was established on damaged grassland after World War I.  The camp had medical triage, and military storage as well as providing safe harbor for troops.  Camp "New York" is still in operation as a military camp, but known as Camp "Suippes."
